description: Lists subscription targets in Amazon DataZone.

parameters.name: domainIdentifier
parameters.description: The identifier of the Amazon DataZone domain where you want to list subscription targets.

parameters.name: environmentIdentifier
parameters.description: The identifier of the environment where you want to list subscription targets.

nested_items.name: items
nested_items.description: The results of the ListSubscriptionTargets action.

nested_items.name: applicableAssetTypes
nested_items.description: The asset types included in the subscription target.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: authorizedPrincipals
nested_items.description: The authorized principals included in the subscription target.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp of when the subscription target was created.

nested_items.name: createdBy
nested_items.description: The Amazon DataZone user who created the subscription target.

nested_items.name: domainId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the Amazon DataZone domain in which the subscription target exists.

nested_items.name: environmentId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the environment of the subscription target.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The identifier of the subscription target.

nested_items.name: manageAccessRole
nested_items.description: The manage access role specified in the subscription target.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the subscription target.

nested_items.name: projectId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the project specified in the subscription target.

nested_items.name: provider
nested_items.description: The provider of the subscription target.

nested_items.name: subscriptionTargetConfig
nested_items.description: The configuration of the subscription target.

nested_items.name: content
nested_items.description: The content of the subscription target configuration.

nested_items.name: formName
nested_items.description: The form name included in the subscription target configuration.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The type of the subscription target.

nested_items.name: updatedAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp of when the subscription target was updated.

nested_items.name: updatedBy
nested_items.description: The Amazon DataZone user who updated the subscription target.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: When the number of subscription targets is greater than the default value for the MaxResults parameter, or if you explicitly specify a value for MaxResults that is less than the number of subscription targets, the response includes a pagination token named NextToken. You can specify this NextToken value in a subsequent call to ListSubscriptionTargets to list the next set of subscription targets.
